{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you pull in Leviathan with a fishhook or tie down its tongue with a rope?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you put a cord through its nose or pierce its jaw with a hook?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will it keep begging you for mercy? Will it speak to you with gentle words?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will it make an agreement with you for you to take it as your slave for life?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you make a pet of it like a bird or put it on a leash for the young women in your house?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will traders barter for it? Will they divide it up among the merchants?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can you fill its hide with harpoons or its head with fishing spears?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If you lay a hand on it, you will remember the struggle and never do it again!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Any hope of subduing it is false; the mere sight of it is overpowering."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "No one is fierce enough to rouse it. Who then is able to stand against me?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who has a claim against me that I must pay? Everything under heaven belongs to me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "I will not fail to speak of Leviathan's limbs, its strength and its graceful form.",
          "speaker": "God"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who can strip off its outer coat? Who can penetrate its double coat of armor?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Who dares open the doors of its mouth, ringed about with fearsome teeth?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Its back has rows of shields tightly sealed together;"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "each is so close to the next that no air can pass between."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "They are joined fast to one another; they cling together and cannot be parted."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Its snorting throws out flashes of light; its eyes are like the rays of dawn."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Flames stream from its mouth; sparks of fire shoot out."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Smoke pours from its nostrils as from a boiling pot over burning reeds."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Its breath sets coals ablaze, and flames dart from its mouth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Strength resides in its neck; dismay goes before it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The folds of its flesh are tightly joined; they are firm and immovable."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Its chest is hard as rock, hard as a lower millstone."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When it rises up, the mighty are terrified; they retreat before its thrashing."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The sword that reaches it has no effect, nor does the spear or the dart or the javelin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Iron it treats like straw and bronze like rotten wood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Arrows do not make it flee; slingstones are like chaff to it."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 29,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "A club seems to it but a piece of straw; it laughs at the rattling of the lance."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 30,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Its undersides are jagged potsherds, leaving a trail in the mud like a threshing sledge."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It makes the depths churn like a boiling caldron and stirs up the sea like a pot of ointment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It leaves a glistening wake behind it; one would think the deep had white hair."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Nothing on earth is its equal— a creature without fear."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "It looks down on all that are haughty; it is king over all that are proud."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}